{
  "texts": [
    "However, we observe that at least one vocabulary adaptation strategy improves over CPT-Only in high OOV (13 out of 16 settings) and high novelty (in all 8 setting); thus necessitating the need for vocabulary adaptation.",
    "RQ3: Vocabulary adaptation helps in high OOV concentrations in reference summaries and source documents.",
    "We observe that vocabulary adaptation (best of MEDVOC-LLM and ScafFix) outperforms BASE in fourteen out of sixteen settings.",
    "For these settings, the average performance improvement over BASE is, 8.74% and 14.64% for Llama-2 and Llama-3.1 respectively.",
    "Thus, MEDVOC-LLM is the best vocabulary adaptation strategy in scenarios of high OOV concentration in reference summaries and source documents."
  ]
}